      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "Hard to knock the recent consistency of LOUIEVILLE LASS (4) having recorded two wins and three seconds from the past five starts. Took advantage of the inside barer when she scored at Ballarat last week, getting home by 5 metres. Draws wider but must rate as a big chance again. I AM HARRO (8) has been coming from wider on this row of late and hasn't been too far off the placegetters at his last two outings, finishing fourth in a higher-graded race last start at Shepparton. Looks suited here so can be right in the finish. POPPY POPSTAR (1) has come from much wider barriers at her las two attempts so could be a big improver from this draw. MACHO MAORI (3) draws well and must be respected after coming from the back line to score last start by 2.7 metres at this circuit and distance.",
